# 1. Document Purpose

This document defines the proposed Salesforce solution architecture and design for the Dealership Lead Management Transformation project.

The solution leverages Salesforce Automotive Cloud to automate lead management processes, improve customer engagement, streamline dealership operations, and provide real-time business insights.

This document serves as a reference for business stakeholders, solution architects, Salesforce administrators, developers, and QA teams.

---

# 2. Business Objectives

The solution aims to achieve the following objectives:

* Centralize lead management activities.
* Improve lead response times.
* Automate lead assignment and qualification.
* Increase lead conversion rates.
* Improve customer experience.
* Eliminate duplicate customer records.
* Provide management reporting and analytics.
* Standardize dealership operations across branches.

---

# 3. Current Challenges

| Challenge              | Impact                    |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------- |
| Manual lead assignment | Delayed customer response |
| Multiple lead sources  | Data inconsistency        |
| Duplicate records      | Poor customer experience  |
| Manual follow-ups      | Missed opportunities      |
| Limited reporting      | Lack of visibility        |
